title: A Brief Guide to Common Public Records
description: This article provides an overview of various types of public records, including voter registration records, city elections records, assessor records, county recorder records, superior court clerk records, municipal court clerk records, U.S. District Court records, Secretary of State records, Department of Motor Vehicle records, building permits, city business licenses, Department of Consumer Affairs records, Federal Aviation Administration records, Security and Exchange Commission records, and U.S. Postal Service records.
